cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.GR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with 3D facial landmark localization from a single image. The use of neural networks for regression and the stacked hourglass network suggest that it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of volumetric representation and 3D convolution network suggest that it could also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories.
